Linear Search in array
Write a program to search for a specific element in an array and print "Yes" if the element is present, otherwise print "No".

Input Format
The first line contains an integer 
n
n, the length of the array and 
k
k, the element to be search.
The second line contains 
n
n space-separated integers representing the elements of the array.
Output Format
Print "Yes" if the element 
k
k is present in the array.
Print "No" if the element 
k
k is not present in the array.
Sample 1:
Input
Output
8 1
3 5 1 4 5 6 5 6
Yes
Sample 2:
Input
Output
3 4
1 2 3
No


import java.util.*;
import java.lang.*;
import java.io.*;
class Codechef
{
	public static void main (String[] args) throws java.lang.Exception
	{
		Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
		int n=sc.nextInt();
		int s=sc.nextInt();
		int a[]=new int[n];
		for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
		    a[i]=sc.nextInt();
		}boolean f=false;
		for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
		    if(a[i]==s){
		        f=true;
		        break;
		    }}
		if(f){
		    System.out.println("Yes");
		}else{
		    System.out.println("No");
		}
	}
}
